<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4747063>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 3. Map of the geographic distribution from IUCN and georeferenced occurrence records from GBIF (grey crosses) for the subgenus Sonora, including S. episcopa, S. semiannulata and S. taylori. The top of the map has images of the uniform (a), banded (b), striped (c), and mimetic (d) morphs of Sonora episcopa. The side panel depicts S. taylori without (e) and with (f) a black cap on the head. The bottom panel depicts the uniform (a), banded (b), striped (c), and mimetic (d) morphs of S. semiannulata. Photos by C. L Cox (a–f, h) and A. R. Davis Rabosky (g, i, j). Colours of circular points on the map correspond to the phylogenetic tree in Figures 1 and 2." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4747063/files/figure.png" .

